is_specific_enough (boolean): evaluate using the ENTIRE conversation above.
- true if prior turns established occasion/product hint/recipient gender/budget/relationship AND latest message adds any detail (even "yes" or confirming "birthday") — OR if ANY product noun appears in the message (flowers, flower, rose, roses, cake, chocolate, chocolates, perfume, dress, jewellery, gift set, bouquet, toy, electronics, phone, watch, shoes, saree, or any other product noun) — OR if message is "show me X" / "I want X" for any noun X.
- false only if truly no useful signal exists anywhere yet.
- If false, set intent to "clarify" instead of "gift"/"search".

Output schema (strict, no extra fields):
{"language":"...","intent":"...","occasion":"...","budget_lkr":null,"refined_query":"...","gift_recipient_gender":null,"gift_recipient_relation":null,"emotional_context":null,"order_number":null}